      <div class="who-desc-wrap">
        <div class="who-desc" data-domain="science">
          <p class="who-desc-name">Health Science</p>
          <p class="who-desc-body">I studied biological sciences at <a href="http://stanford.edu/">Stanford</a>, and ranked first in my class, achieving a <a href="https://www.beckman-foundation.org/programs/beckman-scholars/">Beckman scholarship</a> for my <a href="https://www.jneurosci.org/content/19/19/8630.short">published work</a> in neuroscience and electrophysiology. I went on to found <a href="https://www.healifyapp.com/">Healify</a> and eventually worked directly with patients as a <a href="https://www.bloomharmony.org/">somatic therapist</a>, treating chronic pain and anxiety. The science of how humans actually change has become both my academic foundation and how I approach all of my professional work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="who-desc active" data-domain="product">
          <p class="who-desc-name">Product &amp; UX Design</p>
          <p class="who-desc-body">I spent twenty years building consumer and enterprise products for popular brands such as <a href="http://apple.com/">Apple</a>, <a href="http://intuit.com/">Intuit</a>, <a href="https://www.realtor.com/">Realtor.com</a>, and <a href="https://www.capitalone.com/">Capital One</a>, reaching over 100 million users. I drove results and won awards: a 14% increase in paid conversions at Realtor.com ($45M incremental revenue), 20% fewer support calls at Intuit, and 300% ROI lift for Capital One. I learned how to optimize for KPIs, but even more importantly, how to ask the right questions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="who-desc" data-domain="ai">
          <p class="who-desc-name">Agentic AI</p>
          <p class="who-desc-body">Agentic AI <em>is new to all of us</em>. But after I got over the initial shock of realizing it could <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/anthropic-ceo-predicts-ai-models-233113047.html">fully automate my job</a>, I started getting innovative with it. Agentic AI now feels like a natural evolution of my career, the co-creative ally I have been seeking all along. I started designing, building, and architecting <a href="https://habitualos.com/">applications with AI</a> nearly full-time in 2024, and have been on a mission ever since: <strong><em>to extend human capacity in everyday life</em></strong> in deep partnership with AI.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
(function () {
  const groups = document.querySelectorAll('#who .who-circle-group');
  const panels = document.querySelectorAll('#who .who-desc');
  function activate(domain) {
    const already = document.querySelector('#who .who-circle-group.active');
    if (already && already.dataset.domain === domain) return;
    groups.forEach(g => {
      if (g.dataset.domain === domain) {
        g.classList.remove('active');
        g.parentNode.appendChild(g);
        requestAnimationFrame(() => requestAnimationFrame(() => g.classList.add('active')));
      } else {
        g.classList.remove('active');
      }
    });
    panels.forEach(p => p.classList.toggle('active', p.dataset.domain === domain));
  }
  groups.forEach(g => {
    g.addEventListener('click', () => activate(g.dataset.domain));
    g.addEventListener('keydown', e => { if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') activate(g.dataset.domain); });
  });
  const defaultActive = document.querySelector('#who .who-circle-group.active');
  if (defaultActive) defaultActive.parentNode.appendChild(defaultActive);
})();
</script>

<!-- How I Work: Process -->
<section class="section" id="process">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">How I Work</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">From first conversation to production. How a typical engagement actually goes.</p>

    <div class="process-layout">

      <div class="process-steps-col">
        <div class="process-step active" data-step="assessment" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Discovery">
          <span class="process-step-num">01</span>
          <span class="process-step-name">Discovery</span>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step" data-step="creative" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Creative Sessions">
          <span class="process-step-num">02</span>
          <span class="process-step-name">Creative Sessions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step" data-step="prototyping" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Rapid Prototyping">
          <span class="process-step-num">03</span>
          <span class="process-step-name">Rapid Prototyping</span>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step" data-step="research" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Research">
          <span class="process-step-num">04</span>
          <span class="process-step-name">Research</span>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step" data-step="production" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="Production Integration">
          <span class="process-step-num">05</span>
          <span class="process-step-name">Production Integration</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="process-panels-col">
        <div class="process-panel active" data-step="assessment">
          <h3 class="process-panel-title">Discovery</h3>
          <p class="process-panel-body">Before any creative work, I want to understand the real problem — not just the brief. That means conversations with stakeholders, reviewing existing data, and identifying where the stated need and the actual need diverge. This is often where the most valuable work happens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-panel" data-step="creative">
          <h3 class="process-panel-title">Creative Sessions</h3>
          <p class="process-panel-body">Collaborative working sessions where I bring initial concepts and provocations. Fast, generative, no polish. The goal is to find the direction worth pursuing, not to present finished thinking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-panel" data-step="prototyping">
          <h3 class="process-panel-title">Rapid Prototyping</h3>
          <p class="process-panel-body">With agentic tools, I can move from concept to working prototype in hours. This collapses the feedback loop dramatically — instead of reviewing wireframes, teams can react to something real. That speed isn't just efficiency; it changes what questions you can ask.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-panel" data-step="research">
          <h3 class="process-panel-title">Stakeholder & End User Research</h3>
          <p class="process-panel-body">Validation that runs alongside building, not after it. Qualitative interviews, usability sessions, and stakeholder alignment checks woven into the process rather than bolted on at the end. The most expensive mistake in product is solving the wrong problem with precision.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-panel" data-step="production">
          <h3 class="process-panel-title">Production Integration</h3>
          <p class="process-panel-body">I can take work all the way to production — code, agents, APIs. No handoff required unless the team wants one. The best outcome is something live that real people use, not a deck that describes what it could be.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
(function () {
  var steps  = document.querySelectorAll('#process .process-step');
  var panels = document.querySelectorAll('#process .process-panel');
  function activate(el) {
    var step = el.dataset.step;
    steps.forEach(function (s)  { s.classList.toggle('active',  s.dataset.step === step); });
    panels.forEach(function (p) { p.classList.toggle('active', p.dataset.step === step); });
  }
  steps.forEach(function (s) {
    s.addEventListener('click', function () { activate(s); });
    s.addEventListener('keydown', function (e) { if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') activate(s); });
  });
})();
</script>

